sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J331021
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Source of this part is based off of the peking 2013 team that was detecting tuberculosis too.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: WE have created a plasmid that turns napthalene into salycate through the degrader, then what happens is it goes to the bigger Nahr_operon and form there it triggers the wintergreen smell which tells us that the subject has tuberculosis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: What we did was change the color promoter from Part:BBa_K228004 to a color promoter which creates a wintergreen smell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gilles Yvan Buck

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: WOBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This system is composed of devices <bbpart>J45120</bbpart> and <bbpart>J45320</bbpart>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This system designed by the MIT 2006 iGEM team and generates mint smell by biosynthesizing salicylic acid from chassis-produced metabolites (chorismate) and then converts salicylic acid into methyl salicylate (wintergreen scent).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We recommend use of strain <bbpart>BBa_J45999</bbpart> as it does not produce indole. Indole is responsible for the foul smell of wt e.coli, and masks the wintergreen scent produced by J45600.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: MIT iGEM 2006

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K228004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is constrcuted by PCR from the plasmid kindly provided by Voigt Lab in UCSF.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a salicylate inducible promoter part. The activator protein is right upstream but in a opposite direction of the regulated promoter. In the presence of salicylate, the promoter can be activated.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There is no termoinator downstream of the NahR coding sequence, but it has no effect on parts that are in the same direction as the pSal promoter. However, if coding gene is placed upstream of this part and in the same direction as NahR, it may cause unwanted expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lin Min

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacI+pL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The PLlac 0-1 promoter is a hybrid regulatory region consisting of the promoter P(L) of phage lambda with the cI binding sites replaced with lacO1. The hybrid design allows for strong promotion that can nevertheless be tightly repressed by LacI, the Lac inhibitor (i.e. repressor) (BBa_C0010) ([LUTZ97]). The activity of the promoter can be regulated over a >600-fold range by IPTG in E.Coli DH5-alpha-Z1 (same paper reference).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
hybrid promoter design to create strong promoter that is, at the same time, highly repressible. note that the upstream operator installed in this hybrid is slightly different than the one in the original source (Lutz and Bujard, 1997). the most upstream operator region is slightly truncated in the represillator version, so that both operators in the hybrid are the same sequence. see references for details. also, the sequence has been truncated after the transcriptional start site.

LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and increase transcription. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Neelaksh Varshney, Grace Kenney, Daniel Shen, Samantha Sutton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pchBA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: isochorismate pyruvate-lyase and isochorismate synthase (pchBA); converts chorismate to salicylate
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pchBA is found in pseudomonas. The plasmid was kindly sent to the MIT iGEM team by Dr. Cornelia Riemmann from the Universite de Lausanne.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pchBA codes for proteins used to generate salicylic acid. It doesn't make a fusion protein, even though the coding regions overlap; the RBS for pchA is located at the end of the coding region of pchB.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: MIT IGEM 2006

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BSMT1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SAM:benzoic acid/salicylic acid carboxyl methyltransferase I; converts salicylic acid to methyl sali
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Species: Petunia x hybrida from Genbank; (also available: A. thaliana and N. suaveolens)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for BSMT enzyme to convert Benzoic acid/salicylic acid to methyl benzoate and methyl salicylate. This part is phBSMT1 from Petunia x hybrida.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Boyuan Zhu
